## Root cause fixed

ClickHouse `DateTime64(3, 'UTC')` rejects ISO 8601 strings with `T`/`Z` (e.g. `2026-04-01T00:00:00.000Z`). It requires space-separated format (`2026-04-01 00:00:00.000`). This caused all trends queries to return 500 when hitting a real ClickHouse instance.

## Changes

**`src/lib/trends.ts`** — two fixes:
1. `computeEndExclusive` now returns `YYYY-MM-DD 00:00:00.000` by manually constructing the string from `Date.UTC` components (month rollover still handled correctly).
2. `start` param changed from `` `${start}T00:00:00.000Z` `` → `` `${start} 00:00:00.000` ``.

**`src/lib/__tests__/trends.test.ts`** — 3 new unit tests added verifying the exact timestamp format, written before the fix.

